trend_summary: Between earliest and latest imagery, suburban housing estates spread outward, replacing forest and cropland, while road grids and commercial clusters densified. Built-up footprints expanded mainly north and central corridors, reducing open farmland. Tree cover within neighborhoods remains but contiguous rural fields shrink. Overall environment shifts toward a moderately continuous suburban fabric.
notable_changes: Large new residential subdivisions appear in the northern sector, filling former woodland.
Central corridor shows widening highways and new junctions, improving connectivity.
